title._content: Tom Morris, skipping champion (taken for Greater Union Theatres), 28 June 1937, by Sam Hood

tag.raw: State Library of New South Wales
tag.author: 29454428@N08

description._content: "Tom Morris, who will attempt to skip from Sydney to Brisbane, via the Pacific Highway, will set out from the General Post Office at noon to-day. He has already skipped from Melbourne to Adelaide and back (1000 miles) and from Melbourne to Sydney in 28 days." SMH 28/6/1937 Format: Photograph Find more detailed information about this photograph: acms.sl.nsw.gov.au/item/itemDetailPaged.aspx?itemID=20740 Search for more great images in the State Library's collections: acms.sl.nsw.gov.au/search/SimpleSearch.aspx From the collection of the State Library of New South Wales www.sl.nsw.gov.au

note._content: he does not look very happy
